        {
            "block_label": "figure_title",
            "block_content": "<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Table 6. Quantization results of a visual language model OpenFlamingo-9B (Awadalla et al., 2023) on COCO Captioning datasets. Activation-aware Weight Quantization outperforms existing methods under zero-shot and various few-shot settings, demonstrating the generability to different modalities and in-context learning workloads. Activation-aware Weight Quantization reduces the quantization degradation (32-shot) from 4.57 to 1.17 under INT4-g128, providing 4× model size reduction with negligible performance loss.</div>\n",
